The Chronicle Chronicle Reporter An assailant believed to be an artisanal miner detonated an explosive device in a house in Bulawayo’s Luveve suburb on Tuesday night where three men were conducting bible studies in a fight over a woman. <img class="size-full wp-image-515125" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/10/explossive-detonate-in-Luveve4.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="300" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/10/explossive-detonate-in-Luveve4.jpg 450w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/10/explossive-detonate-in-Luveve4-360x240.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /> Part of the damage to the house It is believed the suspected artisanal miner was targeting one of the three men with whom he is involved in a love triangle. The three men escaped unhurt but the explosive device destroyed part of the wall to the house, window panes and part of the roof. More to follow…